Miss Saigon is coming to the Joseph Anzalone Theatre December 9th until December 12th!

Miss Saigon tells the tragic tale of a doomed romance involving an Asian woman abandoned by her American lover. The setting of the plot is the 1970s Saigon during the Vietnam War, and tells the story of a romance between an American GI and a Vietnamese bargirl. The musical is based on the Opera Madame Butterfly.

Wednesday, December 9th @ 3:30 P.M. ($12)
Thursday, December 10th @ 7 P.M. ($15)
Friday, December 11th @ 7 P.M. ($15)
Saturday, December 12th @ 2 P.M. ($12)
Saturday, December 12th @ 8 P.M. ($15)

Tickets can be purchased by visiting: http://bit.ly/1icP134

